  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6752.59 sitting above the GEX flip at 6714 but trapped between massive negative gamma walls at 6745-6765, dealers are in full amplification mode and likely buying this move higher while being short gamma. The regime flip to BREAKOUT combined with the massive -13B total GEX and detected wall break suggests dealers will continue mechanically buying rallies toward the 6800 positive gamma ceiling where they'll flip to selling pressure. Key inflection points are the 6800 max positive gamma level above (where dealer buying turns to selling) and any pullback toward 6714 GEX flip, below which dealer hedging flips from amplifying to dampening.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect volatile trending moves with strong upside momentum until 6800, then potential reversal pressure.",
